  sodium: 6 g
  serving size: 410
---

Pop your #kettle{} on to boil. Then, pour the boiling @water{200%ml} for the bulgur into a #measuring jug{} and add the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Stir to dissolve.

Slice the @halloumi{1} block into six slices. Pop into a #mixing bowl{}, drizzle on the @red wine vinegar{1} and add half the @smoked paprika{1.5}. This is your marinade! Gently rub the flavours into the cheese and keep to one side.

Halve, peel and slice the @echalion shallot{1} into thin half moons. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, then remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into 1cm pieces. Grate the @lemon{1/2} zest and roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all).

Heat a splash of oil in a #large saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Fry the red pepper, ~{5%minutes}. Add the shallot, stir and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Then, stir in the garlic, @ground coriander{1.5} and remaining smoked paprika and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the vegetable stock, bring to the boil and add the @bulgur wheat{100%g}. Cover with a #lid{}, remove from the heat and leave for ~{10-15%minutes}, or until the water has completely soaked into the wheat.

Halve the lemon and squeeze the juice from one half into a #bowl{} big enough to hold the rocket. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and mix in the @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Keep to one side, we will dress the rocket later.

Heat a #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil). Add the @flaked almonds{25%g} and toast until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. Be careful, they burn easily so stir frequently. Then transfer to a #small bowl{}. Increase the heat to medium-high and add a splash of oil. Lay in the halloumi and cook until golden, ~{3%minutes} each side (fry in batches if your pan is small). Remove from the heat and pour in the marinade and the @honey{1}. Stir to coat the halloumi.

Fluff up the bulgur with a #fork{} and stir in the parsley and the toasted flaked almonds. Add a pinch of lemon zest, some lemon juice, salt and black pepper to taste. Share the bulgur wheat between your #bowls{}. Toss the @wild rocket{1} in the dressing and serve on top of the bulgur. Finish with the halloumi and any juices from the pan. Enjoy!

> The marinade on this halloumi is something of a taste sensation. Sharp red wine vinegar, smoked paprika and sweet honey are balanced perfectly with the saltiness from the halloumi.

> Nutty bulgur, crunchy flaked almonds and peppery rocket are the dream accompaniment to this deliciously nutritious weeknight dinner.